title: Weekly Jobless Claims Sink Slightly to 1.51 Million, Higher Than Expected
caption: breitbart.com
message: New claims for unemployment benefits fell to 1.508 last week, data from the Department of Labor showed Thursday. This is the twelfth consecutive week of initial claims above 1 million. Prior to March, initial claims had never risen as high as 700,000.
